### Formula (Excel – English Functions)
```excel
=LET(
  heir,
    SCAN(
      [@[Employee Name]],
      SEQUENCE(10),
      LAMBDA(acu, val,
        XLOOKUP(acu, [Employee Name], [Manager Name], 0, 0)
      )
    ),
  fil,
    FILTER(heir, heir<>0, ""),
  ord,
    SORTBY(fil, SEQUENCE(ROWS(fil)), -1),
  TEXTJOIN(" > ", TRUE, ord, [@[Manager Name]], [@[Employee Name]])
)
Notes
SEQUENCE(10) defines the maximum hierarchy depth.
Increase this value if deeper organizational structures are expected.

The formula is fully dynamic and updates automatically.

2) Direct Reports
Purpose
Count how many employees report directly to a given employee.

Logic
Counts rows where the employee appears as a manager.

Formula
