=COUNTIFS([Manager Name], [@[Employee Name]])
3) Total Reports
Purpose
Calculate the total number of employees reporting under a given employee, including both direct and indirect reports.

Logic
Use the Reporting Hierarchy column.

Count how many hierarchy paths contain the employee’s name.

Subtract one to exclude the employee’s own row.

Formula
excel
Copiar código
=COUNTIFS(
  [Reporting Hierarchy],
  "*" & [@[Employee Name]] & "*"
) - 1
Key Strengths
Uses pure Excel formulas with no automation or scripts.

Fully dynamic and easy to audit.

Demonstrates advanced use of LET, SCAN, and dynamic arrays.

Ideal for small to medium-sized organizational datasets.

Limitations
Maximum hierarchy depth must be predefined.

Cycles in reporting relationships are not handled.

Requires clean and consistent employee naming.

